1
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:05,982
GLORY

2
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:20,789
<i>The toll has been collected.</i>

3
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:45,688
SUMMER OF 2022

4
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:32,610
JAEPYONG BUILDING

5
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:47,417
CAUTION! SCHOOL

6
00:02:47,441 --> 00:02:56,441
RTNNJ

7
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:05,852
SEMYEONG STREET, NO. 71
PARADISE APARTMENTS

8
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,267
Just moved in?

9
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,399
How are you?

10
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:56,361
You have finally arrived.

11
00:03:56,444 --> 00:03:58,446
It took you a long time.

12
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:02,992
Welcome.

13
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:06,287
This flower is called the devil's trumpet.

14
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:10,917
The one they call the angel's trumpet
because he plays facing the ground.

15
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:15,004
And this one is called the devil's trumpet
because he plays facing the sky.

16
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:18,549
God thought it was rude.

17
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:22,637
Maybe that's why it only smells at night.

18
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:27,600
I have to break earthen pots
before I throw them away.

19
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:53,626
<i>Yeon-jin, I miss you.</i>

20
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:56,254
<i>Do you remember</i>

21
00:04:57,213 --> 00:05:00,717
<i>that I used to hate summer?</i>

22
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:05,763
<i>Fortunately, I moved away</i>
<i>before it got warmer.</i>

23
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:09,392
<i>I've been putting photos together since yesterday,</i>

24
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:12,395
<i>but I'm slow</i>
<i>because their faces are charming.</i>

25
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:15,898
<i>I started imagining</i>

26
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:17,859
<i>that you will one day</i>

27
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:22,322
<i>open the door and come in here.</i>

28
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:31,748
What is all this?

29
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:35,084
This is Jae-jun and Sa-ra.
Photos of all of us.

30
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:37,420
Sorry.

31
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,672
Who are you?

32
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,636
It's me, Yeon-jin. It's me.

33
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:49,849
You haven't changed at all.

34
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,894
You're still rude.

35
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:56,397
You should take off your shoes
when you enter someone's home.

36
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:06,949
You gave me a new reason to kill you.

37
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:08,910
You should have at least recognized me.

38
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:12,538
To kill me?

39
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:13,873
You to kill me?!

40
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:15,208
Yes, I will kill you.

41
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:18,461
I will do my best to kill you.

42
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:21,130
So come quickly, Yeon-jin.

43
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:23,174
I'm already here.

44
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:28,221
Do you want to hear

45
00:06:29,138 --> 00:06:31,057
how I became like this

46
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:34,143
while we wait for you?

47
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:39,315
An official report has been submitted.

48
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:41,692
Guardians must come. It's a procedure.

49
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:45,405
I'll just scold her, no worries.

50
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:47,323
Okay, I'll call you.

51
00:06:49,575 --> 00:06:50,410
Park Yeon-jin.

52
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:54,580
-That?
- Why are you beating your friend?

53
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,416
Don't come for that again.

54
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,251
Your mother is coming.

55
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,502
We are not friends.

56
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:00,753
Let me ask you something.

57
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,423
What are you and my mom doing?

58
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:06,384
We are friends from school.

59
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:08,803
So you're her errand boy?

60
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:11,389
That's why you helped her with the divorce.

61
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:14,183
And gathered evidence of my father's adultery.

62
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:17,395
I thought you slept with my mom.

63
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,110
Let's go!

64
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:26,821
Deliveries are waiting! Get up and walk!

65
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:29,157
You embarrass me. I said you are not coming.

66
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:32,326
Everything will be fine if they make up and hug each other.

67
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,661
Sa-ra, come.

68
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:45,965
How can I help?

69
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:48,676
I am Dong-eun's guardian. Her class teacher.

70
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:53,723
Hey.

71
00:07:54,307 --> 00:07:56,142
Did you come in your school uniform?

72
00:07:56,225 --> 00:07:59,061
You called the police because of a simple dogfight?

73
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,730
The deputy director knows.

74
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,610
I'll deal with you later. Come.

75
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:07,153
Take me too.

76
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:08,905
I have been an orphan for seven days.

77
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,574
My parents traveled.

78
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,910
- They play golf.
- Don't?

79
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:16,996
You should have called me.

80
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:18,748
I'll take him too.

81
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:19,999
Good.

82
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,669
I was wondering why you were still here.

83
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:25,421
How do you eat?

84
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:27,507
- I have a housekeeper.
- Is it?

85
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:35,640
Today was an important day.

86
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:38,726
You have disappointed me greatly.

87
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,063
I didn't expect the police.

88
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,232
That's why I'm disappointed.

89
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,567
You couldn't solve the poor thing.

90
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:52,698
I told you
to only hang out with Jae-jun.

91
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:53,908
And Sa-rom.

92
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:56,702
The shaman told you

93
00:08:57,495 --> 00:09:01,040
to avoid people with O in their name
because they bring misfortune.

94
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:03,876
I mean Son Myeong-o and Choi Hye-jeong.

95
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:06,963
Come in. We're running late.

96
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,139
MOON DONG-EUN
SUNGHAN SECONDARY SCHOOL

97
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:07,982
Here we have Dong-eun!

98
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:11,402
The same Dong-eun you see every day!

99
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:16,657
Welcome.

100
00:10:20,369 --> 00:10:22,622
Sorry for harassing you.

101
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:25,708
I wanted to apologize.
You don't get angry anymore?

102
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:30,546
You shouldn't have called the police.
You scared us.

103
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,468
Speaking of which, Dong-eun,

104
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:38,804
will you be checking from now on?

105
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:41,140
is the curler hot?

106
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:47,480
Let me go!

107
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:49,732
This is a crime! Let me go!

108
00:10:50,232 --> 00:10:53,235
You are doing us a small favor.
How is that a crime?

109
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,154
She already apologized to you.

110
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:57,239
I'm just wondering if he's hot.

111
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,246
Is it hot?

112
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:08,250
I think he's ready.

113
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:09,960
Let's see.

114
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:16,467
Help! Help me!

115
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:19,261
Don't bother.

116
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:22,056
Scream all you want. No one will hear you.

117
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:23,307
No one will come.

118
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,603
The professor gave us the keys.

119
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:36,821
Why are you doing this to me?

120
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:40,199
Why on earth are you doing this to me?

121
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,493
I'm sick of hearing that.

122
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:45,913
Why do they always ask that?

123
00:11:46,497 --> 00:11:48,290
I do it because I'm untouchable.

124
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,751
Nothing changes for you.

125
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:52,420
Just look at yourself.

126
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:55,589
You made a fuss at the station,
and now you're here again.

127
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:57,675
Is there any change?

128
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:01,971
No one will protect you, Dong-eun.

129
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:05,474
Not the police, not the school, not even the parents.

130
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,977
What do we call such people?

131
00:12:08,644 --> 00:12:10,521
Disenfranchised.

132
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:15,526
Do you live in a boarding house?

133
00:12:15,609 --> 00:12:18,320
Because of you, I know what it means to live in a motel.

134
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:20,614
He must pay when the Moon is full.

135
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:23,743
Like in a fairy tale!

136
00:12:23,826 --> 00:12:27,246
Dong-eun must be my good fairy.

137
00:12:27,329 --> 00:12:29,999
He's checking to see if my curler is hot.

138
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:33,544
Let me go!

139
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,337
Let me go!

140
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:37,506
- Let me go!
- Shut up!

141
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:39,800
- Let go!
- Myeong-o, shut her up.

142
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:40,718
Let me go!

143
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,889
You are too loud in public.

144
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:54,857
IT'S BORING ME

145
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:10,247
Hydrogen peroxide?

146
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:13,292
Just give it to me.

147
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:15,795
I have a stain on my blouse.

148
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,129
What stain?

149
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:20,633
Maybe from the blood?

150
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:26,096
Give me hydrogen peroxide.

151
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:33,395
What happened? Who did it?

152
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:35,856
Did you tell your classmate?

153
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,068
I've seen a scar like that before.

154
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:42,571
If you can't do it alone,
I will go with you to report it.

155
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:44,824
Who did it?

156
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,464
Yes, mom?

157
00:14:01,715 --> 00:14:03,300
I'll call you.

158
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:08,264
That's what I did.

159
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,642
And the one before that.

160
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,445
<i>You know what, Yeon-jin?</i>

161
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:30,870
<i>Your daughter likes to look at the world upside down.</i>

162
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:35,374
<i>Does she think people will understand her</i>

163
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:39,169
<i>when the world turns upside down,</i>
<i>even mixed the colors?</i>

164
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:48,846
You have the same shoes as my mom.

165
00:14:56,979 --> 00:14:58,063
So it's you.

166
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:01,275
Park Yeon-jin's daughter, Ha Ye-sol.

167
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:03,444
You know my mom?

168
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:06,906
I think about her every day.

169
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:11,493
Hate sometimes resembles longing.

170
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:14,121
You can't get rid of her.

171
00:15:14,204 --> 00:15:15,289
Hatred?

172
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:18,459
I don't know that word. What does it mean?

173
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,300
What does "hate" mean?

174
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:01,335
How funny!

175
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:12,721
What is it?

176
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:14,932
Are you going to run away?

177
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:36,161
<i>Her eyes that darken when she is excited.</i>

178
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:38,414
Where have you been for so long?

179
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:41,417
I missed you a lot.

180
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,502
<i>A smile that stretches her lips.</i>

181
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:46,380
<i>Every hair of her wonderful hair.</i>

182
00:16:47,423 --> 00:16:48,924
<i>When you add it all up,</i>

183
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,343
<i>you get a picture of hatred.</i>

184
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:58,851
She took off her clothes before going in!

185
00:16:58,934 --> 00:17:01,603
We're shit. Shame on us.

186
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:03,355
Move over.

187
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:06,442
Your piggy bank?

188
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,777
It was in a box with rice.

189
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:11,864
- I couldn't believe it.
- Give it back to me.

190
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:14,950
Oh, no.

191
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,369
Is Dong-eun angry?

192
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:19,580
Nicely caught.

193
00:17:20,789 --> 00:17:21,999
It's full.

194
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:25,294
Seriously? How sad.

195
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:26,462
Dong-eun.

196
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:29,965
You are very thrifty.

197
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,468
Crazy scumbag. What did you take this time?

198
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:34,053
Syrup or glue?

199
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:38,307
Stop it! Don't do that!

200
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,685
Dong-eun is terribly rich!

201
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:44,313
- There are 200,000 won.
- You pay for all this?

202
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:48,233
You are rich! You don't need that money!

203
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:52,821
Please. Give it back to me, Yeon-jin.

204
00:17:54,531 --> 00:17:56,533
I see you are being polite now.

205
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:58,160
Good.

206
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:00,829
I'll give you your money back.

207
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:05,167
But I want you to dance while we drink.

208
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:07,836
Then I won't even touch the money. Can you?

209
00:18:08,378 --> 00:18:10,380
-What?
- Dance, I said!

210
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:14,176
Song and dance go well with alcohol.

211
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:17,262
What is it? You don't want to?

212
00:18:19,681 --> 00:18:22,184
If you really don't want to, there is another way.

213
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,312
I found this here.

214
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:29,608
You're all in a coma.

215
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:32,277
But if you pretend to be proud,

216
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:36,949
you'll be in an even bigger coma.

217
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:39,493
So dance.

218
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:41,745
Humiliated.

219
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:46,875
If you don't want to, it doesn't matter.

220
00:18:49,878 --> 00:18:53,048
When I saw you today, Dong-eun…

221
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:57,719
You have beautiful legs.

222
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:08,981
I'll pick a song.

223
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:11,817
I have many in my cell phone.

224
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:37,593
AMBULANCE

225
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:46,268
TEMPORARILY CLOSED
DUE TO THE DEPARTURE OF THE NURSE

226
00:22:28,263 --> 00:22:30,182
Seriously? When?

227
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:33,518
I'll call you.

228
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:38,690
Dong-eun dropped out of school.

229
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,276
She put our names on the form.

230
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:45,655
She gave it to the deputy director,
who is bothering our professor.

231
00:22:47,783 --> 00:22:48,992
From the body?

232
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:51,828
She listed us by that
who beat her more?

233
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:55,207
Which one am I?

234
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:57,501
This is serious, you understand?

235
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:02,798
Hey!

236
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:04,549
Jae-jun! Yeon-jin!

237
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:05,967
Come.

238
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,768
<i>Crazy bastard!</i>

239
00:23:15,769 --> 00:23:17,771
<i>If you want to leave, do it quietly.</i>

240
00:23:17,854 --> 00:23:20,524
<i>And you haven't sinned anything? Nothing at all?!</i>

241
00:23:21,024 --> 00:23:23,777
<i>If it happened,</i>
<i>something is wrong with you!</i>

242
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,737
<i>Please correct the form!</i>

243
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:36,081
PRINT FORM

244
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:37,999
If the principal sees this,

245
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,752
it will affect your judgement, Mr. Kim.

246
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:43,755
I know that. Please.

247
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:53,515
What is this?

248
00:23:55,183 --> 00:23:57,102
What is that reason?

249
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:59,438
Violence at school.

250
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:03,066
It's Yeon-jin's fault, Sa-ra's,
Jae-jun, Hye-jeong and Myeong-o.

251
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,696
You did nothing.

252
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:09,197
Tongue for teeth!

253
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:11,700
Did they break your arm or leg?

254
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:13,952
You don't have any broken limbs.

255
00:24:14,035 --> 00:24:15,620
What kind of violence is that?

256
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:17,664
What do you mean, I didn't do anything?

257
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:19,916
You're crazy, you understand?

258
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,669
It's not terrible if friends slap each other.

259
00:24:22,752 --> 00:24:23,753
And why is it okay?

260
00:24:25,589 --> 00:24:26,923
slap a friend?

261
00:24:28,758 --> 00:24:29,593
What?

262
00:24:29,676 --> 00:24:32,512
You said
that your son is in teacher training college.

263
00:24:35,098 --> 00:24:38,185
It's okay to be slapped by friends...

264
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:44,232
I was good to you.

265
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,152
And now you're looking for a beating.

266
